# subctl projects — declarative per-account project bindings.
#
# Each non-comment line declares one project: a tmux session bound to a
# specific Claude account, in a specific directory. `subctl projects start`
# will launch all of them in parallel (or just one if you specify a name).
#
# Format:
#   name | account_alias | project_dir | description
#
# - name:           short tmux-friendly slug (lowercase, no spaces)
# - account_alias:  must exist in ~/.config/subctl/accounts.conf
# - project_dir:    absolute path or ~/path; expanded at launch time
# - description:    optional, free-form
#
# Example (delete the leading "# " to enable):
#
# argent     | claude-semfreak  | ~/code/argent-core         | ArgentOS work
# holace     | claude-jason     | ~/code/holace              | personal-injury SaaS
# titanium   | claude-titanium  | ~/code/titanium-thing      | Titanium MSP work
